benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/paymentMethods/{paymentMethodId}/setDefault - Set the default payment method

covered: Valid Request: Multiple scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05) demonstrate successful updates with various parameter configurations.
Non-Existing Resource: Coverage of 404 for non-existent account/paymentMethod, mismatched method-owner, and accounts with no payment methods (TC08, TC09, TC10, TC21).
Concurrency: Scenario TC22 validates concurrent requests across different payment methods and maintains consistency.
Authorization: Tests TC11 and TC12 cover missing header and unauthorized access.
Query Parameters: Tests TC02, TC03, TC14, TC15, TC24 cover combinations of payAllUnpaidInvoices, pluginProperty, additional headers, and empty pluginProperty.
Error Handling: Tests TC06, TC07, TC11, TC12, TC13, TC18, TC19 exercise 400/401/403/404/503/504/422-like responses and error messages.
Audit Logging: TC04 validates that audit logs capture reason and comment when present.
Input Validation: Tests TC06, TC07, TC23 validate UUID formats and detect partial UUIDs or invalid UUID lengths.
Regression: TC20 and TC21 verify fixes/regressions for default state and edge-case behavior with zero/no payment methods.
Performance: TC17 and TC22 cover performance implications and response time under load or concurrency.
Accessibility: TC25 ensures API documentation and error messages are accessible as per accessibility standards.
Edge Case Coverage: TC19 (injection), TC16 (min/max UUID values), TC15 (max pluginProperty entries) and TC24 (empty pluginProperty) address several boundary and security edge cases.
gaps: Rate Limiting: No tests validating rate limiting or throttling of PUT requests.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) for this PUT operation.
403 Forbidden Coverage: No test specifically validating insufficient privileges (beyond 401).
Race Conditions on Same Resource: No explicit test ensuring race-free updates when multiple clients update the same account/method in parallel.
Invalid PluginProperty Types: No tests for non-string or invalid pluginProperty entries.
500 Internal Server Error: No test simulating 500 error; only 503/504 covered.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests to verify proper throttling behavior under bursty PUT requests.
Add tests for caching headers to ensure proper caching semantics for idempotent PUT operations (ETag, Cache-Control).
Add a 403 Forbidden test to cover insufficient privileges in addition to 401.
Add a race-condition test for updates to the same account/method in parallel to ensure atomicity.
Add tests for invalid pluginProperty types (non-string, null) and edge-case values in arrays.
Add tests simulating 500 Internal Server Error to verify proper handling.
